race.comment: RED BEAUTY (9) has put back-to-back wins together over this course and distance range and it's hard to knock mares in form. Winning rider Fenlon sticks in the irons following that last-start victory and should be going very close again. KAI MONDO (4) loves this track and trip only missing a drum in once seven attempts. Gets 2kg off with the claim and can feature prominently despite the wide draw. UNIVERSAL HARMONY (3) goes well for hoop McIver who has three wins and two placings from just five steers. Hard to toss in this suitable race. TORQUE I TEE (1) should get the run of the race from the inside alley and has to be included in calculations. HIGHGROUND (8) has won two of his past three and shouldn't be discounted lightly.
